          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The samples included two copper samples and three",
                "aluminum samples with a sandwich structure, which",
                "were wrapped in cadmium foil to absorb thermal",
                "neutrons. The copper and aluminum samples are all",
                "natural ones >99.999% in purity. The thicknesses of",
                "each copper sample and each aluminum sample are 0.20",
                "and 0.02 cm, respectively. The diameter of all the",
                "samples is 2.00 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A low-background high-purity germanium (HPGe)",
                "detector (ORTEC, 46-TP41590A, diameter 82 mm, length",
                "55.4 mm). The HPGe detector was pre-calibrated for",
                "energy and detection efficiency using standard gamma",
                "sources of 60Co and 137Cs."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For each neutron energy, the samples were",
                "irradiated for about 10h. The three aluminum samples",
                "were measured separately with each measurement",
                "duration of about 10 min after the cooling of about",
                "60 min. The two copper samples were measured",
                "simultaneously (one on top of another) using the HPGe",
                "detector after the cooling of about 30 days, and they",
                "were measured twice (with their positions exchanged)",
                "in two runs with both measurement durations of about",
                "48 h."
              ]
            }
          ],
